channel.title: Help With Silab & Compiling
channel.description:
I currently have this problem with Silab's web client:
I load it up on IE and i go through all the loading etc; get to the login in screen and type in my details but then: When i press login and it access' the server it comes up with 'Loading - Please wait' and has the chat box etc. It freezes me here and nothing i do can fix it. Please help.
Also:
Compiling, this is a really nooby thing to ask but no matter what i can't get my compilers to work.
Most guides talk about JDK & JRE but for some reason i only end up with both being JRE and not having Javac.exe
If you can help with either please say.
